{"id": "EUVD-2024-28185", "enisaUuid": "61c0ae19-bff8-32b3-929c-4aa57d346418", "description": "FastDDS is a C++ implementation of the DDS (Data Distribution Service) standard of the OMG (Object Management Group). Prior to versions 2.14.1, 2.13.5, 2.10.4, and 2.6.8, when a publisher serves malformed `RTPS` packet, heap buffer overflow occurs on the subscriber. This can remotely crash any Fast-DDS process, potentially leading to a DOS attack. Versions 2.14.1, 2.13.5, 2.10.4, and 2.6.8 contain a patch for the issue.\n", "datePublished": "2024-05-13T14:45:28", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-02T01:32:05", "baseScore": 8.2, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:H", "references": ["https://github.com/eProsima/Fast-DDS/security/advisories/GHSA-qcj9-939p-p662", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Y2bGvP3UIOJCLh_XEURLdhrM2Sznlvlp/view?usp=sharing", "https://vimeo.com/907641887?share=copy"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-30259"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 1.1, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "9033f9cf-c185-3fa4-a2f2-52d4aaa9306a", "product": {"name": "Fast-DDS"}, "product_version": "2.13.0, < 2.13.5"}, {"id": "a62fd83a-2a8f-368f-a753-5f1f4e8da26e", "product": {"name": "Fast-DDS"}, "product_version": "< 2.6.8"}, {"id": "acaca13e-e0a9-3961-8c60-1f255397674b", "product": {"name": "Fast-DDS"}, "product_version": "= 2.14.0"}, {"id": "bc616734-7cf3-3210-ae73-3389c3978b61", "product": {"name": "Fast-DDS"}, "product_version": "2.10.0, < 2.10.4"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "ce94c024-3c78-3bc4-90c8-36d117990a02", "vendor": {"name": "eProsima"}}], "isExploited": false}